      "writtenOn": "2020-12-15T02:57:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In general, conceptually, Tast should not be a source of truth of features.\nTast is testing framework, which respects the existing board features/configurations.\nSo, maintaining boardnames does not sound a long term support.\n\nWe implemented boardnames for SoftwareDeps, and we expect it is used for short term workaround in general, e.g., in some cases some features are unstable due to unknown reasons on specific boards. In such a case, Boardname support of SoftwareDeps allows developers to split the test into two, without adding USE flags representing each board that does not help actual development.",
      "parentUuid": "9ee4daf0_a0adf051",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 107,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 107,
